article.description: — Cameron Johnson had 21 points as Stephen F. Austin rolled past Lamar 102-72 on Saturday.
article.headline: Johnson carries Stephen F. Austin past Lamar 102-72
article.linkText: Johnson carries Stephen F. Austin past Lamar 102-72
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- — Cameron Johnson had 21 points as Stephen F. Austin rolled past Lamar 102-72 on Saturday. Roti Ware had 17 points for Stephen F. Austin (9-2, 5-0 Southland Conference), which won its sixth straight game. Gavin Kensmil added 17 points. David Kachelries had 13 points. Lamar totaled 37 first-half points, a season high for the team. Kasen Harrison had 12 points for the Cardinals (3-11, 2-4). Quinlan Bennett added 12 points. David Muoka had 13 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
